        "leadershipRole": "<p>\n    Co-founder and Chief Science Officer\n</p>",
        "quotefromLeader": "",
        "leadershipBio": "<p>\n    Michael and his brother Steven Rothman co-founded PeraHealth in 2005 to develop software capable of detecting subtle changes in patientsâ health that often are missed because of multiple shift changes and patient handoffs in hospitals.\n</p>\n<p>\n    They were motivated by the avoidable death of their mother, Florence Rothman, who died in a Florida hospital in 2003 after a deteriorating trend went undetected following a relatively low-risk surgical procedure. With his brother (an engineer specializing in system design and data visualization), Michael used his background as a Ph.D. chemist with 30 years experience in data analysis to develop a complex algorithm that produces a score capturing gradual but important changes in patientsâ conditions in easy-to-read graphs.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Previously, during an 18-year career at IBM Corp., Michael was an engineer in computer science and artificial intelligence at IBMâs T.J. Watson Research Laboratory and developed models that led to a doubling of chip yields at the companyâs Microelectronics Division. As manager and executive consultant for the IBM Consulting Group, he specialized in transforming mathematical results into business strategies for major banks and financial institutions.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Later, as senior vice president for strategic information for First USA Bank, Michael established a more effective approach to interact with customers and developed a database to better determine their preferences.\n</p>\n<p>\n    In 2000, he founded Michael Rothman &amp; Associates to focus on data analysis and product development through consulting, patent filing and joint ventures. Projects have included developing a system generating customized discharge forms for hospitals, helping determine cash flow and profitability for a pharmaceutical companyâs newly introduced drugs, and pro bono work analyzing puppy mortality data for a guide dog school.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Michael received bachelorâs and masterâs of science degrees in chemistry from Brown University and a Ph.D. in chemistry at the University of Michigan.\n</p>",
        "leadershipImage": {
          "sys": {
            "type": "Link",
