        "introSummary": "<p>\n    UHS Becomes Most Recent Health System to Join Community of PeraTrend Users\n</p>",
        "body": "<p>\n    CHARLOTTE, N.C., April 17, 2014 â Nationally recognized as a leader in advanced treatment options using new technology and clinical research, San Antonio-based University Health System recently announced their partnership with PeraHealth. UHS plans to deploy PeraHealthâs PeraTrend throughout their 496-bed hospital.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Powered by the Rothman Index, PeraTrend extracts key information from the electronic health record and provides clinicians with a real-time understanding of patient condition. UHS leaders view PeraTrend as a key tool in supporting the systemâs journey toward constantly improving the quality of care.\n</p>\n<p>\n    âWe saw an opportunity to make our EHR data actionable,â said Dr. Alton Powell, UHS Chief Medical Information Officer. âAs a public hospital, we believe that it is our responsibility to serve Bexar County and the community to the best of our ability. We are excited about what we can achieve with PeraHealth.â\n</p>\n<p>\n    âOur decision was very simple,â said Bill Phillips, UHS Chief Information Officer. âWith PeraTrend, we are able to maximize the use of our existing electronic medical record and for pennies on the dollar, make that data actionable.â\n</p>\n<p>\n    âWe are delighted to collaborate with a hospital as prestigious as University Health System,â said Stephanie Alexander, Chief Executive Officer of Charlotte-based PeraHealth. âThe systemâs dedication to providing exceptional care and outcomes for their patients and community is underscored by UHSâ Magnet status and many accolades. We are excited at how clinicians at UHS will surely find innovative ways to use the real time clinical decision support of PeraTrend and the Rothman Index.â\n</p>\n<p>\n    About University Health System<br>\n    Owned by the people of Bexar County, UHS is a nationally recognized academic medical center. In partnership with UT Medicine San Antonio, the practice plan of The University of Texas Health Science Center, it is consistently recognized as a leader in advanced treatment options, new technologies and clinical research. UHS is Bexar County and South Texasâ first and only health system to earn Magnet status. Magnet hospitals and health systems offer patients reassurance they are being cared for by a team with a proven track record for providing excellent care and positive outcomes for their patients. For more information, visit <a href=\"http://www.universityhealthsystem.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.universityhealthsystem.com</a>.\n</p>\n<p>\n    About PeraHealth<br>\n    PeraHealth is transforming healthcare through the intelligent use of data. By leveraging the Rothman Index, a validated patient acuity score, PeraHealth software solutions enable healthcare providers to identify at-risk patients sooner for earlier intervention. Leading hospitals and health systems utilize PeraHealthâs real-time, predictive analytics to improve quality and reduce costs. Clinical results include lowering mortality rates by as much as 30%. For more information, visit PeraHealth.com and @PeraHealth.\n</p>",
        "releaseDate": "2014-04-17",
        "pDFPressRelease": null,
        "mediaContact": "",
        "title": "University Health System Announces Partnership with PeraHealth to Drive Quality Patient Care",
        "slug": "university-health-system-announces-partnership-with-perahealth-to-drive-quality-patient-care"
      }
    },
