        "leadershipRole": "<p>\n    <em>SVP,</em> <em>Client</em> <em>Services</em> <em>and</em> <em>Chief</em> <em>Customer</em> <em>Service</em>\n</p>",
        "quotefromLeader": "",
        "leadershipBio": "<blockquote>\n    <blockquote>\n        <em>We are excited to welcome Carolyn Scott to the PeraHealth team! Reporting to me, Carolyn will be serving as our SVP/Chief Customer Officer leading our relationship management and clinical adoption services. Though traveling often, she work remotely from Southlake, TX (between Dallas and Ft. Worth). Carolyn starts today, joining Carolyn M at UHS in San Antonio and then meeting Michael and I in Houston for Grand Rounds throughout the Houston Methodist System. Many of you got a chance to meet her at our Summit meeting in June (and possibly the Baseball game!). Also, Carolyn has made it to several calls learning more about our customers and team since the Summit.<br>\n        <br>\n        Prior to joining PeraHealth, Carolyn provided consulting services in the areas of Value-Based Performance and Health Data/Analytics. She spent 6 years as Service Line Vice President, Quality &amp; Safety, for Premier, Inc. She was responsible for the strategic direction, planning and execution of healthcare quality and safety service line, including consulting services and large scale collaboratives and clinical networks. Prior to Premier, Carolyn spent 7 years in various consulting and relationship management roles with KPMG and Vizient (formerly VHA). Additionally, she worked as a registered nurse and various nursing administration roles in the Dallas area.<br>\n        Carolyn holds an MHA from the University of Texas at Arlington, a BS in Nursing from Texas Christian University, a MS in Secondary &amp; Higher Education Consulting &amp; Guidance from Texas A&amp;M and a BA in Business and Finance from University of Texas El Paso. Wow! Lots of time in Texas!<br>\n        Carolyn is married to Gary, they have two sons, one grandson, and two Westies! She loves sports, cooking/baking, volunteering and jigsaw puzzles! And if you couldnât tell by her education, she is a âproud Texanâ, living in the State all her life.<br>\n        Please join me in welcoming Carolyn to our team!</em><br>\n    </blockquote>\n</blockquote>",
        "leadershipImage": null,
        "title": "Carolyn Scott",
        "slug": "carolyn-scott"
      }
