      "fields": {
        "introSummary": "<p>\n    Signature Integrates Rothman Index into Meditech MAGIC EHR to Improve Clinical Outcomes, Enhance Nurse-Physician Communication and Reduce Cost of Care\n</p>",
        "body": "<p>\n    CHARLOTTE, N.C., April 8, 2014 â PeraHealth is pleased to announce that Signature Healthcare will deploy PeraTrendâ¢ for real-time clinical decision support as part of a broad strategy to improve care, outcomes and cost for the system and the surrounding community. Serving the Southeastern Massachusetts community, Signature Healthcare is a multi-specialty hospital and physician group comprised of Brockton Hospital and Signature Medical Group.\n</p>\n<p>\n    PeraTrend calculates the Rothman Index, the next generation patient acuity measure that automatically extracts a range of key EHR data to generate a single, actionable score that gives clinicians real-time insight into a patientâs condition. A key factor for Signature Healthcare in choosing PeraTrend is the ability of the Rothman Index to measure patient condition across all disease states and patient populations. âWe saw a means to leverage existing patient data to provide our clinicians with enhanced information to drive better care for our community,â said Kim Hollon, Signature Healthcareâs President and Chief Executive Officer. âWe firmly believe that PeraTrend will allow us to meet our operational and financial goals while continuing to strive for the best clinical outcomes possible and high satisfaction in terms of patient experience.â\n</p>\n<p>\n    âWe are thrilled that Signature Healthcare will be joining some of the nationâs top hospitals and healthcare providers that are committed to providing quality patient care,â said Stephanie Alexander, Chief Executive Officer of Charlotte-based PeraHealth, Inc. âBy integrating the Rothman Index into the Meditech MAGIC platform, Signature will bring real time clinical decision support across the system, improving cliniciansâ ability to provide quality care while making more efficient use of system resources.â\n</p>\n<p>\n    About Signature Healthcare<br>\n    Signature Healthcare is a multi-specialty hospital and physician group comprised of Brockton Hospital and Signature Medical Group with more than 150 physicians practicing in 11 ambulatory locations. Signature is a not-for-profit community based healthcare delivery system in Southeastern MA providing the full range of high quality primary care, specialty care, hospital care and related ancillary services on a coordinated basis delivered at a low cost. For more information, visit <a href=\"http://www.perahealth.com/discover/news/signature-healthcare-selects-perahealths-peratrend-advance-quality-patient-care/www.signature-healthcare.org\">www.signature-healthcare.org</a>.\n</p>\n<p>\n    About PeraHealth<br>\n</p>\n<p>\n    PeraHealth is transforming healthcare through the intelligent use of data. By leveraging the Rothman Index, a validated patient acuity score, PeraHealth software solutions enable healthcare providers to identify at-risk patients sooner for earlier intervention. Leading hospitals and health systems utilize PeraHealthâs real-time, predictive analytics to improve quality and reduce costs. Clinical results include lowering mortality rates by as much as 30%. For more information, visit PeraHealth.com and @PeraHealth.\n</p>",
        "releaseDate": "2014-04-08",
        "pDFPressRelease": null,
        "mediaContact": "",
        "title": "Signature Healthcare Selects PeraHealthâs PeraTrend to Advance Quality Patient Care",
        "slug": "signature-healthcare-selects-perahealth-s-peratrend-to-advance-quality-patient-care"
      }
