        "jobResponsibilities": "<ul>\n    <li>Build and sustain relationships with key customer physician contacts to drive ownership and commitment\n    </li>\n    <li>Speak the âlanguage of medicineâ with customers and external experts\n    </li>\n    <li>Develop and deliver physician adoption services during the initial implementation of the PeraHealth solutions, in conjunction with the overall implementation team\n    </li>\n    <li>Develop and deliver compelling descriptions of how PeraHealth solutions add value to clinicians\n    </li>\n    <li>Identify areas to promote use of PeraHealth technology in creating efficiencies for physicians and improving quality care\n    </li>\n    <li>Meet with key customer players to test ideas and/or gain commitment. Conducts site visits as needed\n    </li>\n    <li>Update customers on key company initiatives and strategic opportunities\n    </li>\n    <li>Maintain focus on customer and company objectives and value proposition\n    </li>\n    <li>Build credibility and foster business partner relationships through interaction with customers, communicating relevant content/industry focused information\n    </li>\n    <li>Systematically review progress to measurable goals to ensure value is added\n    </li>\n    <li>Help evaluates client outcomes and reviews trends/numbers\n    </li>\n</ul>",
        "qualifications": "<p>\n    <br>\n</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Board certified physician (any specialty)\n    </li>\n    <li>8 years experience of progressive healthcare leadership that includes direct involvement in the use, development and deployment of electronic health records or the use of technology in quality and safety improvement in health systems\n    </li>\n    <li>Experience in the implementation of production-based clinical information systems with a focus on informatics and clinical decision support\n    </li>\n    <li>Knowledge of current regulatory requirements and current trends relating to Electronic Medical Records management\n    </li>\n    <li>Demonstrated ability to supervise successful projects and teams in order to meet deadlines\n    </li>\n    <li>Proficiency with PCs and knowledge of informatics to be able to understand IT issues and converse intelligently with health system IT personnel\n    </li>\n    <li>Superior writing and presentation skills and the ability to listen and communicate with individuals at all levels.\n    </li>\n    <li>An advanced degree in medical informatics is preferred\n    </li>\n</ul>",
