        "leadershipRole": "<p>\n    CIO, Senior Vice President of Technology &amp; Services\n</p>",
        "quotefromLeader": "",
        "leadershipBio": "<p>\n    Edward is a technologist and business strategy executive with more than 20 years of experience in creating competitive advantages by using business intelligence and analytics.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Prior to joining PeraHealth in September of 2012, Edward co-founded MicroStrategy and held various positions including Vice President of Customer Management and Director of Predictive Analytics. His responsibilities included consulting with clients on big data, data mining and predictive analytics in healthcare, retail, financial services and other industries. He leads all technical support, sales operations, and quality engineering efforts.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Additionally, Edward also was vice president of data and analytics for an investment company in Mexico, leading trading analytics for an equity and commodity investments. In addition, he co-founded eMonterrey in Mexico, which specialized in cost-competitive business intelligence and quality engineering software services.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Edward received a bachelorâs of arts degree in economics and political science from Duke University.\n</p>",
        "leadershipImage": null,
        "title": "Edward Yurcisin",
        "slug": "edward-yurcisin"
      }
