        "location": "<p>\n    Charlotte, NC\n</p>",
        "travelExpectation": "<p>\n    40%\n</p>",
        "jobResponsibilities": "<ul>\n    <li>Manage the overall implementation of the PeraHealth solution with multiple customers:\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Focus on driving customer delight â from building the relationships needed at the CXO level to leading a successful technical implementation to the clinical deployment. Take responsibility for overall planning, execution and success of complex technical and clinical deployment projects.\n            </li>\n            <li>Establish and foster trusted partnership relations with existing clients through exceptional delivery of PeraHealth solutions and services, and continuous maintenance of executive-level relationships; seek client references for new sales accounts, and ensure select key clients are continuously involved in PeraHealth User Groups, executive thought leadership workshops and other relevant marketing programs.\n            </li>\n            <li>Communicate externally and internally with project and customer stakeholders to keep them updated with the status and any roadblocks or potential issues.\n            </li>\n            <li>Own the overall customer implementation.\n            </li>\n            <li>Call on internal technical and clinical teams, as well as SMEs when appropriate, to support the customer.\n            </li>\n            <li>Assist with escalated customer issues and project issues as identified or requested by the customer through direct support or through the support of the PeraHealth SMEs\n            </li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n    <li>Provide leadership and mentoring in an innovative and fast paced environment.\n    </li>\n    <li>Travel to customer sites within the US is required up to 40%\n    </li>\n    <li>Support other customer related projects that require project management services\n    </li>\n</ul>",
        "qualifications": "<ul>\n    <li>10+ years experience of project management of software implementations. Healthcare project management experience a plus.\n    </li>\n    <li>Experience with needs assessment, software design, implementation, testing and validation, support, and reporting. Keen attention to detail.\n    </li>\n    <li>Proven ability to effectively communicate with Executive Sponsors, clinicians, and IT\n    </li>\n    <li>Leadership, facilitation, team building, and change management skills a must\n    </li>\n    <li>Ability to listen to clients in order to deliver high quality customer service\n    </li>\n    <li>EHR/EMR and/or clinical experience a plus\n    </li>\n    <li>Minimum of bachelorâs degree\n    </li>\n</ul>",
        "additionalSkills": "<ul>\n    <li>Experience working and managing projects with remote technical teams\n    </li>\n    <li>Strong interpersonal skills including the ability to work collaboratively and manage across team boundaries and drive organizational improvements\n    </li>\n    <li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills\n    </li>\n</ul>",
        "applicationDetails": "<p>\n    To apply for this position, please <a href=\"mailto:recruiting@perahealth.com\">click here</a> to email your cover letter and resume to <a href=\"mailto:recruiting@perahealth.com\">recruiting@perahealth.com</a>.\n</p>",
